Queen and if the Queen take the Bishop White will take the Rook on a8. Can
Black save the game?} 1. Bg5 Rxa1 {The best chance. Black wants to sacrfice
the Queen for the Rook and the Knight and create fortress.} 2. Bxd8 Rxf1+ 3.
Kxf1 Rxd8 4. g3 (4. Qc6 {This is a bad move becouse White will lose the Queen.}
Ne6 5. Qxb5 Rd1+ 6. Ke2 Nd4+ 7. Kxd1 Nxb5 $17 {Black is wining.}) 4... Ne6 {
Now you can see a perfect picture. Black place his pieces ( Rook ond Knight on
the best squares and protect every pawn! It is hard for White to make any
progress.} 5. Qb7 g6 6. Qxb5 c5 7. h4 h5 8. b4 cxb4 9. Qxb4 Kg7 10. Kg2 Kg8 11.
Qc3 Ra8 12. Qf3 Rb8 {You can see a very nice picture. All Black pawns are
protected, Rook and Knight perfectly placed and now Black can move his King to
g7 and g8. White can not create anything and the game is draw. Black saves the
game.} 1/2-1/2

